04:55.629 --> 04:57.338
- Hello?
- Dad, it's Robert.

04:57.423 --> 04:58.673
Robert.

04:58.757 --> 05:01.050
Dad, listen, things aren't looking good—

05:06.098 --> 05:08.808
- I'm sorry.
- Oh, well, that's a shame.

05:08.893 --> 05:10.852
That's a real shame.

05:10.936 --> 05:14.689
Yeah, you're gonna miss out
on having some fancy wine...

05:14.773 --> 05:17.066
and filet mignon steak—

05:17.151 --> 05:21.154
- Have you heard from the others?
- Yeah. So far all of them are coming—

05:21.238 --> 05:23.198
some Friday night, some Saturday morning.

05:23.282 --> 05:25.491
I'm sorry I can't—

05:25.576 --> 05:27.577
Yeah, I'm sorry too, Robert.

05:27.661 --> 05:30.163
You gotta get back to that orchestra, Son.

05:30.247 --> 05:33.082
- I will. You take care.
- Okay. You take care too.

05:33.167 --> 05:35.835
Okay. Okay.

05:56.941 --> 05:59.108
Dad, hi. I can't stop right now.

05:59.193 --> 06:00.818
I'm back on stage in a few minutes.

06:00.903 --> 06:05.031
The producers are flying in from Paris
and want to see the original cast...

06:05.115 --> 06:08.243
so I just can't get away this weekend.

06:08.327 --> 06:11.704
I'm sorry. I know I haven't been home
since the funeral...

06:11.789 --> 06:14.499
but I'm trying, I promise.

06:14.583 --> 06:16.501
I love you. I'm thinking ofyou.

06:16.585 --> 06:18.336
Big kiss.

06:20.256 --> 06:21.881
Hey, Dad, it's Amy.

06:21.966 --> 06:24.175
I'm really sorry to have to do this...

06:24.260 --> 06:27.053
but things have just gotten
really crazy at the agency...

06:27.137 --> 06:29.555
and Jack's sick with a fever.

06:29.640 --> 06:32.892
He missed school today.
So between one thing and another...

06:32.977 --> 06:35.228
we're not gonna be able
to make it this weekend.

06:35.312 --> 06:37.021
I'm really sorry, Dad.

06:38.983 --> 06:41.401
And to make things worse,
I spoke to David today...

06:41.485 --> 06:44.195
and he can't make it either.

06:44.280 --> 06:46.864
He's got a lot going on—
a painting or something.

06:46.949 --> 06:52.412
But, anyway, I promise
we'll make it to you soon. Okay?

06:52.496 --> 06:54.122
Love you.

07:06.427 --> 07:10.763
Well, you can't. You can't just go flying
all across the country- not in your condition.

07:10.848 --> 07:14.475
Who said anything about flying?
What about buses? What about trains?

07:14.560 --> 07:16.060
I'm worried about your lungs, Frank.

07:16.145 --> 07:19.564
Don't worry about my lungs.
Worry about your lungs. My lungs are fine.

07:19.648 --> 07:23.443
Fibrosis of the lungs requires you
to take things easy. Now, you know that.

07:23.527 --> 07:26.571
I'm just going on the buses,
on the trains.

07:26.655 --> 07:29.407
You picked the wrong job, Frank. I mean—

07:29.491 --> 07:32.201
Breathing in humidified PVC.
all those years.

07:33.662 --> 07:36.581
You know, it's just about seeing
the family, you know.

07:36.665 --> 07:41.002
Jean always kept
in touch with everybody, and now it's—

07:41.086 --> 07:43.087
You know how it is. Now it's down to me.

07:44.882 --> 07:47.508
- How you managing on your own?
- I'm fine.

07:47.593 --> 07:49.177
- Fine?
- Fine. Yeah, I'm fine.

07:49.261 --> 07:50.887
Fine?

07:51.722 --> 07:53.723
You know, when I lost my wife...

07:53.807 --> 07:56.684
I found myself talking to her
like she was still there.

07:56.769 --> 07:58.394
Went on for months.

07:59.438 --> 08:01.522
"Where the hell are my shorts?"

08:01.607 --> 08:04.984
No. No, no,
there's nobody there. Talking to myself.

08:05.069 --> 08:06.736
Crazy, huh?

08:08.280 --> 08:10.365
- You do that, Frank?
- No.

08:10.449 --> 08:11.908
No? No?

08:13.118 --> 08:14.118
Not yet.

08:14.203 --> 08:16.204
Look, you know,
I hear what you're saying. I do.

08:16.288 --> 08:19.499
But this trip,
it's not what you need right now.

08:19.583 --> 08:21.542
You gotta take things easy.

08:21.627 --> 08:23.795
Stay home.

08:23.879 --> 08:26.047
You know what you should do?

08:26.131 --> 08:28.257
Spend more time in the garden.

08:33.472 --> 08:35.681
Ed said it was fine.

08:35.766 --> 08:39.227
He said just take enough medication.

08:39.311 --> 08:42.021
Stick to trains and buses.

08:42.106 --> 08:44.524
And I'll take plenty of pictures...

08:44.608 --> 08:46.609
and I'll bring home the news.

08:49.029 --> 08:51.155
I'll start with David in New York.

08:51.240 --> 08:54.450
And if anything goes wrong,
I'll be right home.

08:57.955 --> 08:59.455
Got my keys...

09:00.457 --> 09:02.125
my wallet.

09:03.627 --> 09:05.128
My keys.

09:06.130 --> 09:08.131
Got my medication.

09:09.967 --> 09:11.467
Camera.

09:13.470 --> 09:15.638
Got my keys.

09:39.204 --> 09:41.581
Next.

09:41.665 --> 09:43.708
New York City. One-way, please.

09:45.127 --> 09:46.752
Eighty-seven dollars.

09:46.837 --> 09:49.839
Eighty-seven dollars. There's a hundred.

09:51.008 --> 09:53.759
- I'm going to see my son.
- Very good.

09:53.844 --> 09:56.762
- Know what he does?
- Absolutely no idea.

09:56.847 --> 09:59.599
- He's an artist.
- Gate 7. Thank you. Next.

09:59.683 --> 10:01.350
Thank you.

10:19.870 --> 10:21.537
What do you think of my work?

10:23.874 --> 10:26.709
You've been looking at it ever since
we left the station.

10:27.711 --> 10:29.295
I'm sorry. I don't understand.

10:29.379 --> 10:33.090
No, don't look at me. Look back
out the window. Tell me what you see.

10:33.634 --> 10:35.176
- Cars.
- No.

10:36.178 --> 10:38.888
- Trees?
- Well, yes, but no.

10:39.973 --> 10:41.057
Houses?

10:43.143 --> 10:47.063
J ust remember that you've been looking at it
ever since we left the station.

10:48.148 --> 10:49.774
Oh, the window. The glass.

10:49.858 --> 10:52.902
No. Not bad, but— That's a start, but—

10:54.071 --> 10:55.571
Birds.

10:56.073 --> 10:58.032
No. Not birds.

11:02.246 --> 11:03.246
Rocks.

11:04.331 --> 11:06.874
No. Rocks. No.
That's ridiculous. Rocks.

11:06.959 --> 11:09.877
You're just guessing.
I'm gonna stick with this lady here.

11:09.962 --> 11:13.172
- I think she has an idea.
- No. Honestly, I really have no idea what you—

11:13.257 --> 11:15.466
You know, just look for the rhythm.

11:19.179 --> 11:22.473
- The telephone poles.
- Close. Close.

11:22.558 --> 11:25.476
- The wire.
- Well, well— Keep going. Keep going.

11:25.561 --> 11:27.979
- Really, I give up.
- No, no, that's— Okay, that's it.

11:28.063 --> 11:30.439
That's it. The wire. That's good.
I mean, I didn't make the wire.

11:30.524 --> 11:33.234
I didn't hang the wire.
But I coated the wire.

11:33.318 --> 11:35.444
I protected it with PVC coating
against the rain...

11:35.529 --> 11:37.863
the moisture, heat— stuff like that.

11:37.948 --> 11:42.034
So what you actually see is not
the wire. It's my PVC coating.

11:42.119 --> 11:45.788
- I ran a thousand miles of wire a week, nonstop.
- Wow.

11:45.872 --> 11:47.790
Nonstop.

11:47.874 --> 11:51.586
You just think for a minute— all the conversations
that have taken place over that wire.

11:51.670 --> 11:54.964
Breaking good news and bad news.

11:56.967 --> 11:58.426
You know.

12:00.470 --> 12:02.096
- Can I show you something?
- Sure.

12:02.180 --> 12:03.806
There are my...

12:05.309 --> 12:06.475
children.

12:07.477 --> 12:09.687
Robert the conductor.

12:09.771 --> 12:12.773
David the artist. Rosie the dancer.

12:12.858 --> 12:14.775
Amy- very high up in advertising.

12:14.860 --> 12:17.820
A million feet of wire to get them
where they are today.

12:19.197 --> 12:20.698
That's a nice picture.

12:20.782 --> 12:22.908
Thank you.

12:22.993 --> 12:25.995
A million feet of wire to get them
where they are today.

12:29.833 --> 12:30.833
Rocks.

12:31.668 --> 12:34.378
Yeah, right. That's right. Rocks.

12:37.758 --> 12:41.427
They were all supposed to visit me.

12:41.511 --> 12:43.429
We were gonna have a family reunion...

12:43.513 --> 12:46.515
and instead they all canceled on me
at the last minute.

13:56.795 --> 13:59.046
You lock yourself out, honey?

14:00.382 --> 14:02.883
No, I didn't lock myself out.
My son lives here.

14:02.968 --> 14:04.635
I'm just waiting for him.

14:04.720 --> 14:07.722
You can come wait with me ifyou want.
I know a place.

14:07.806 --> 14:10.474
- Oh, thank you. That's nice ofyou, but—
- You sure?

14:10.559 --> 14:12.601
- Thank you.
- You want to see my leg?

14:14.938 --> 14:17.022
You want to see mine?

14:37.627 --> 14:38.836
- Come on.
- Here.

14:38.920 --> 14:40.296
Oh, man.

14:41.131 --> 14:44.049
- Oh, dude, I can't believe you, man.
- What?

14:44.134 --> 14:46.302
I can't believe you. All night.

15:24.674 --> 15:25.966
David.

15:35.352 --> 15:37.728
What are you gonna do
when you grow up, huh?

15:37.813 --> 15:40.940
- I want to be a painter and do my pictures.
- Not a painter. Christ.

15:41.024 --> 15:44.860
Painters paint walls, and dogs pee on walls.
You're gonna be an artist.

15:44.945 --> 15:48.739
Artists paint pictures that change people's lives.
Now what are you gonna be?

15:48.824 --> 15:50.741
- An artist.
- That's right. An artist.

15:50.826 --> 15:52.910
- So you're gonna work hard?
- Yes, Dad.

15:52.994 --> 15:56.455
- You're gonna make me proud?
- I'm trying, Dad.

16:15.100 --> 16:18.727
Unfortunately, it's going to be on top
of the coast sometime tomorrow.

16:18.812 --> 16:23.649
Right now, Hurricane Alice
is packing winds of 1 65 miles per hour.

16:23.733 --> 16:26.485
We've got a Category 5 hurricane.
The pressure—

16:26.570 --> 16:28.070
Looks like a bad storm.

16:29.948 --> 16:32.283
A bad storm.

16:32.367 --> 16:34.702
I'm 94.

16:35.579 --> 16:38.330
- I keep away from the doctors.
- Boy.

16:38.415 --> 16:41.750
I have three children, six grandchildren.

16:42.711 --> 16:46.797
They're busy. They're too busy to talk to me.
I gotta make an appointment.

16:46.882 --> 16:49.800
They got lost someplace.

16:49.885 --> 16:52.678
They don't need anybody.

16:52.762 --> 16:55.764
People change. Life is changed.

16:55.849 --> 16:57.892
Today, you shake hands with somebody...

16:57.976 --> 17:01.270
you gotta count your fingers
to make sure you got five fingers back.

17:17.621 --> 17:18.704
- Hi.
- Hi.

17:18.788 --> 17:20.706
- Can I help you?
- Do the bells work?

17:20.790 --> 17:22.207
Yeah.

17:22.292 --> 17:24.752
My son lives in Apartment 9.

17:24.836 --> 17:26.754
I'm not sure if he's home.

17:26.838 --> 17:28.505
- All right.
- Thank you.

18:06.795 --> 18:07.836
David?

19:00.265 --> 19:02.766
Through my sleepless days

19:02.851 --> 19:05.019
I've found

19:05.103 --> 19:09.773
That in my dreamless sleep I'm bound

19:09.858 --> 19:13.902
To one night hear the sound

19:13.987 --> 19:16.363
Ofyou calling

19:16.448 --> 19:20.534
Do not stumble through tonight

19:20.618 --> 19:23.495
Have no fear for me

19:23.580 --> 19:27.791
You won't stumble through tonight

19:27.876 --> 19:30.919
Drownin' in their laughter

19:33.631 --> 19:35.591
This is not good.

19:38.428 --> 19:40.179
Amy, it's Rosie.

19:41.973 --> 19:44.892
- Dad's not answering his phone.
- Well, don't call him...

19:44.976 --> 19:46.894
not till we know
what's going on with David.

19:46.978 --> 19:49.563
- Is there any more news?
- No.

19:49.647 --> 19:53.400
I just had that one call
from Mexico saying he'd been arrested.

19:53.485 --> 19:55.152
I keep leaving messages,
but no one's calling back.

19:55.236 --> 19:57.404
I think we should tell Dad.

19:57.489 --> 19:59.406
Not until we know what's going on.

19:59.491 --> 20:03.243
Just avoid talking to him for a couple days
till we know the facts, okay?

20:03.328 --> 20:05.412
Okay.

20:20.136 --> 20:22.054
- Oh, my God.
- Surprise.

20:22.138 --> 20:25.182
Yeah, definitely. Come on in, Grandpa.

20:29.354 --> 20:31.605
Man. Does Mom know?

20:31.689 --> 20:34.066
No, I hope not. But, hey, look at you.

20:34.150 --> 20:36.110
I thought you were supposed
to be in bed with a fever.

20:36.194 --> 20:38.195
- I don't know. Am I?
- That's what she told me.

20:38.279 --> 20:40.072
Yeah, I think I was.

20:40.156 --> 20:43.492
- It's got a handle.
- Well, of course it's got a handle.

20:43.576 --> 20:44.618
I didn't know that.

20:44.702 --> 20:47.746
- Yeah, it's got wheels.
- Well. Look how big you got.

20:47.831 --> 20:49.331
I know, right?

20:50.333 --> 20:53.127
- Gee.
- Hey, listen.

20:53.211 --> 20:55.212
I'm online.
I'll be back in a minute.

20:55.296 --> 20:57.589
All right. You do your thing.

20:57.674 --> 21:00.717
- Mom's out back.
- Okay. Good.

21:03.638 --> 21:05.681
No, I need to go down there.

21:05.765 --> 21:09.852
Yeah. Can you check out some flights
to see what's available?

21:16.860 --> 21:17.860
Yeah.

21:19.445 --> 21:21.405
Amy .

21:22.532 --> 21:23.657
Dad?

21:30.623 --> 21:33.000
- What are you doing here?
- What do you mean, what am I doing here?

21:33.084 --> 21:35.335
Everybody didn't show up
for the visit, so I said...

21:35.420 --> 21:39.506
- "Ifyou don't come to me, I'm gonna go to you."
- Oh, you crazy man.

21:39.591 --> 21:42.092
Well, look at you. You haven't been well.
You shouldn't be traveling.

21:42.177 --> 21:44.094
- Did you check with the doctor?
- I checked with the doctor.

21:44.179 --> 21:47.097
- You checked with him?
- Of course I checked with the doctor. Jeff home?

21:47.182 --> 21:51.059
No, not yet.
Let me find out when he's coming back.

21:51.144 --> 21:54.229
So, everybody dropped out of the visit?

21:54.314 --> 21:56.899
I didn't realize. I had no idea.

21:58.234 --> 22:00.152
How did you get here?

22:00.236 --> 22:02.404
- You didn't fly, did you?
- No, of course I didn't fly.

22:02.488 --> 22:05.282
I took a train to New York to see David,
and he wasn't there...

22:05.366 --> 22:07.284
so I took a bus here.

22:07.368 --> 22:09.286
You took a bus?

22:09.370 --> 22:10.829
- Yeah.
- To Chicago?

22:10.914 --> 22:13.582
- All by myself.
- Oh, my God. I can't believe it.

22:13.666 --> 22:15.709
Yeah. Jack got better fast.

22:16.711 --> 22:18.337
Yeah. No, he did. Definitely.

22:18.421 --> 22:20.088
It was a 24-hour thing.

22:24.510 --> 22:27.346
- I like the house.
- Yeah. But you've seen pictures.

22:27.430 --> 22:29.473
I've seen pictures.
I haven't seen the house.

22:29.557 --> 22:32.017
- Not the real thing.
- Hey, everyone.

22:33.102 --> 22:35.520
- Hey, Jack.
- How's it goin'?

22:35.605 --> 22:37.856
- Good.
- Jack, why don't you take Grandpa outside...

22:37.941 --> 22:40.400
- and show him your golf-
- You play golf?

22:40.485 --> 22:42.778
Sure. I'm a natural.

22:42.862 --> 22:44.905
- Yeah, I'd like to see that.
- You want to see that?

22:44.989 --> 22:47.199
- Where are you hitting it?
- To that flag over there.

22:47.283 --> 22:48.909
All the way out there?

22:48.993 --> 22:51.245
Oh, boy. Okay.

22:51.329 --> 22:53.288
- My record's three.
- Three?

22:54.916 --> 22:57.584
