your body

39:18.398 --> 39:21.400
Your mind is close behind

39:21.485 --> 39:25.529
There's a teardrop on your shoulder

39:25.614 --> 39:28.115
Says this is the time of times

39:28.200 --> 39:31.535
Could you take a picture of me
against the glass?

39:31.620 --> 39:36.457
It's the time of times again

39:36.541 --> 39:39.210
One more just to— Turn the—

39:39.294 --> 39:41.254
Could you— Yeah.

39:57.646 --> 40:00.022
Okay, everybody. It's a new day.

40:00.107 --> 40:02.566
An opportunity for all of us
to make amends.

40:02.651 --> 40:04.568
So why don't we start at the beginning.

40:04.653 --> 40:07.113
Horns, trumpets,
very percussive in the first section.

40:07.197 --> 40:10.658
Strings, more energy in those bows. Ready?

40:21.378 --> 40:24.839
- It's fine. I'll take you right through.
- Thank you.

40:26.800 --> 40:29.176
They're rehearsing right now.

41:51.718 --> 41:54.720
- Hey, Dad. What are you doing here?
- What am I doing?

41:54.805 --> 41:57.348
I've come to see you conduct.
What are you doing?

41:57.432 --> 41:59.725
I'm rehearsing.

41:59.810 --> 42:02.061
Aren't you conducting?

42:02.145 --> 42:05.231
Not today, no. I'm—

42:05.315 --> 42:07.858
- Playing the drum.
- I am.

42:07.943 --> 42:09.819
It's percussion.

42:10.529 --> 42:12.947
It's what I do.

42:13.990 --> 42:15.950
I thought you were conducting.

42:16.827 --> 42:19.829
Not today.
I'll explain. I should get back.

42:20.997 --> 42:22.998
You just walked off the stage
and nobody noticed?

42:24.376 --> 42:26.544
Come on, stop it. What are you doing here?

42:26.628 --> 42:29.130
I'm visiting. It's a surprise.

42:29.214 --> 42:31.757
I came to spend some time
with my son, the conductor.

42:33.677 --> 42:35.594
That's my cue.

42:35.679 --> 42:38.139
- Well, get back. Get back.
- Okay.

42:53.989 --> 42:56.365
That's very good.

42:56.450 --> 43:00.411
Very good, yeah. Never hit a drum
in my life, and suddenly I'm very good.

43:00.495 --> 43:05.374
Without training, without skill, without
all the musical talent that you have.

43:05.459 --> 43:08.043
Never said I was conducting, Dad.

43:08.128 --> 43:10.296
Yeah, well—

43:10.380 --> 43:11.881
But your mother said you were doing well...

43:11.965 --> 43:15.176
that you were conducting and composing
and doing your music.

43:15.260 --> 43:17.178
I am doing my music.

43:17.262 --> 43:20.222
It's percussion.
And it suits me just fine.

43:21.850 --> 43:24.935
But the drum?

43:25.020 --> 43:27.396
It's low pressure, and I enjoy it.

43:27.481 --> 43:32.067
I get to travel.
The money's fine. I got no ties.

43:33.320 --> 43:36.530
Everybody said that
you had a talent...

43:36.615 --> 43:38.157
that you had a future.

43:39.075 --> 43:41.368
People are polite, Dad. You know,
they don't always tell you the truth.

43:41.453 --> 43:44.872
The truth is,
I was never quite good enough.

43:48.376 --> 43:52.421
But all that education,
and now you're disappointed?

43:52.506 --> 43:54.882
I'm not disappointed.

43:54.966 --> 43:57.510
I'm not disappointed,
but you obviously are.

43:57.594 --> 44:00.888
No, I'm not disappointed.
It just seems like a waste. That's all.

44:00.972 --> 44:04.141
Of what? What's it a waste of?
Ofyour telephone wire?

44:04.226 --> 44:07.686
No, no, it's not that. I didn't say that.

44:07.771 --> 44:11.190
You know, I still compose,
and I conduct in my spare time.

44:11.274 --> 44:14.818
But nobody wants to employ me to do that
professionally. That's just the way it is.

44:14.903 --> 44:17.446
Well, I guess I'm just saying
that it's never too late.

44:17.531 --> 44:21.700
You could keep at it
and go back to studying.

44:21.785 --> 44:24.161
- I could help you out.
- It doesn't work like that, Dad.

44:24.246 --> 44:27.081
If it was going to have happened,
it would have happened by now.

44:28.500 --> 44:32.294
Besides, I'm not sure it's what I wanted.
I think maybe I was doin' it for you.

44:32.379 --> 44:34.296
I don't believe that.

44:34.381 --> 44:37.716
Dad, the point is, this suits me just fine.
This is what I want.

44:41.555 --> 44:44.056
Hey. Hey.

44:45.058 --> 44:48.185
You managing okay at home?

44:48.270 --> 44:50.187
Yeah, I'm cooking every day.

44:50.272 --> 44:53.524
Cooking? Yeah?
Do you know what you're doing?

44:53.608 --> 44:56.110
No, I just make it up.

44:57.821 --> 45:00.823
Well, I thought we could spend
a couple of days together.

45:01.533 --> 45:04.034
Dad, I fly to Europe this evening.

45:04.119 --> 45:07.204
It's a big trip.
We got to pack up this afternoon.

45:07.289 --> 45:09.373
I wish I could, honestly, but— you know.

45:09.457 --> 45:12.626
I'm sorry, Dad.
That would have been great.

45:17.215 --> 45:19.800
Well—

45:27.559 --> 45:31.020
I went to see David in New York.
Is he still at the same address?

45:32.105 --> 45:34.231
Yeah. I think so.

45:34.316 --> 45:37.401
Yeah, I want to check his address
and phone number with you.

45:37.485 --> 45:38.986
Sure.

45:40.905 --> 45:42.948
- I need some fresh air.
- All right.

45:49.122 --> 45:51.957
- Robert, come on. Don't smoke.
- What do you mean, don't smoke?

45:52.042 --> 45:55.836
Don't smoke.
You know better. Come on. Don't smoke.

45:57.964 --> 46:00.049
All right. I won't smoke.

46:00.133 --> 46:02.217
Not in front ofyou. Not if it upsets you.

46:02.302 --> 46:06.347
But, you know,
I do smoke sometimes, just so you know.

46:06.431 --> 46:08.349
Anyway, you used to smoke.

46:08.433 --> 46:11.644
I know I used to smoke.
That's when I didn't know any better. Now I do.

46:11.728 --> 46:13.646
Your mother made me stop too.

46:13.730 --> 46:17.066
You know, I will too.
But occasionally I do smoke.

46:17.150 --> 46:19.485
When I want to quit, I'll quit.

46:19.569 --> 46:22.279
- Hey, Robert.
- Hey, Dave.

46:22.364 --> 46:24.740
Let me get this straight.
You worked in a wire factory...

46:24.824 --> 46:26.909
smoking a couple of packs a day.

46:26.993 --> 46:29.078
But me being a percussionist...

46:29.162 --> 46:33.207
and having an occasional cigarette
isn't good enough for you?

46:33.291 --> 46:34.416
Come on.

46:36.503 --> 46:39.838
You know, Mom used to say, "Make your dad proud.
He works so hard for us."

46:39.923 --> 46:42.841
- And I know you're not proud of me. I know.
- That's not true.

46:42.926 --> 46:44.718
I can feel it. It's fine.

46:44.803 --> 46:47.304
I'm working hard here.
I'm doing the best I can.

46:47.389 --> 46:49.807
- Have your cigarette.
- What?

46:49.891 --> 46:51.892
Have your cigarette. You need it.

46:56.606 --> 46:58.565
No, you know what? I quit.

47:00.318 --> 47:02.820
- Hi, Robert.
- Hey. I just quit smoking.

47:02.904 --> 47:05.572
- Good job.
- Thanks.

47:05.657 --> 47:07.616
I'm not quitting because you want me to.

47:07.701 --> 47:10.869
I'm quitting 'cause
I know you don't think I can.

47:10.954 --> 47:13.539
J ust to make that clear, okay?

47:13.623 --> 47:15.165
Okay.

47:16.626 --> 47:18.836
Anyway, you sounded good on the drums.

47:18.920 --> 47:23.132
I missed a beat when I heard you coming in,
bumping your bag.

47:23.216 --> 47:25.551
You kind of threw me off there.

47:25.635 --> 47:28.721
Well, anyway,
what's a missed beat here and there?

47:28.805 --> 47:30.931
It's good. It sounded very good.

47:32.142 --> 47:33.142
Yeah.

47:34.144 --> 47:35.811
Thanks.

47:38.148 --> 47:41.859
We don't see each other very often.
I wasn't trying to—

47:41.943 --> 47:44.695
- Yeah.
- I'm sorry, you know? I'm just—

47:44.779 --> 47:47.322
Look, you just gave up smoking.
You're gonna be a little edgy.

47:47.407 --> 47:50.534
Is that what it is?

47:50.618 --> 47:52.953
Well, anyway, I'm sorry.

47:53.037 --> 47:54.955
Yeah, well, I'm sorry too.

47:57.083 --> 47:59.585
- Hey, James. I want to introduce you to my father.
- Of course.

47:59.669 --> 48:02.671
- This is James Green, famous conductor.
- Hi, James.

48:02.756 --> 48:05.883
- This is Frank, my dad— very famous dad.
- Hi.

48:05.967 --> 48:09.136
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice meeting you. Good luck with everything.

48:09.220 --> 48:12.306
- Thanks.
- All right. He's busy. He's—

48:14.642 --> 48:17.186
Got a girlfriend you want
to tell me about?

48:17.270 --> 48:20.981
There was someone up until recently.

48:21.065 --> 48:22.983
Not anymore?

48:23.067 --> 48:25.235
You know, she wanted to settle down.

48:25.320 --> 48:28.071
She started talking about babies.

48:28.156 --> 48:30.866
It's difficult with the traveling,
you know.

48:32.494 --> 48:36.288
- There's some girls in the orchestra.
- I noticed.

48:36.372 --> 48:38.791
Oh, yeah? You noticed, huh?

48:38.875 --> 48:41.794
- I got my eye on a couple of 'em.
- A couple, huh? Yeah.

48:43.505 --> 48:46.632
Well, you look after yourself, Robert.

48:46.716 --> 48:49.384
I'm getting the whole family together.

48:49.469 --> 48:52.179
Amy's gonna call you.
But if not, if she forgets...

48:52.263 --> 48:56.016
- you call her and you stay in touch with each other.
- I will. I will.

48:56.100 --> 48:57.976
And you're happy?

48:58.061 --> 49:04.024
Happy? Yeah. I get paid to bang a big,
loud drum all day. Of course I'm happy.

49:06.528 --> 49:08.195
Okay—

49:13.159 --> 49:15.869
Hey, I'm sorry that we couldn't
spend more time together.

49:28.007 --> 49:31.510
Maybe I'm wrong

49:33.555 --> 49:38.016
Amputate sympathy

49:39.185 --> 49:42.771
Strength of my tongue

49:44.274 --> 49:49.236
It's taken that liberty

49:50.738 --> 49:52.823
I don't know. He's—
I'm watching him right now.

49:52.907 --> 49:55.701
He's buying his ticket. He arrives
in Vegas at 1 0:00 tomorrow morning, okay?

49:55.785 --> 49:57.703
Okay. I'll be there.

49:57.787 --> 49:59.788
No, no, no.
He doesn't want you to meet him.

49:59.873 --> 50:02.833
- He wants it to be a surprise.
- Of course I'm gonna. If I want to, I'll meet him.

50:02.917 --> 50:05.335
Rosie, he doesn't—

50:05.420 --> 50:09.506
Okay. But, you know,
he's not gonna like it.

50:09.591 --> 50:12.009
How are you? Are you okay?

50:13.094 --> 50:15.429
Yeah, I guess.

50:15.513 --> 50:18.181
You know, I wanted
to spend some time with him.

50:18.266 --> 50:20.392
I'm free tonight or tomorrow,
but I just can't.

50:20.476 --> 50:23.854
I can't do it. I can't do it.
I don't know what to say to him.

50:23.938 --> 50:27.649
- I know. God, I know.
- Rosie.

50:27.734 --> 50:30.152
- What?
- He's asking about David.

50:30.236 --> 50:33.864
- Okay. I won't say anything.
- No, I mean, there's nothing to say.

50:33.948 --> 50:36.033
What are we gonna say?
We don't know anything.

50:36.117 --> 50:39.953
Play devil's advocate

50:41.331 --> 50:45.042
Never I fear

50:47.045 --> 50:51.256
Pay for it afterwards

50:55.386 --> 50:58.472
How do I feel

51:00.892 --> 51:04.645
A glorified refugee

51:05.813 --> 51:09.816
And nobody ever says

51:09.901 --> 51:12.402
Good-bye

51:15.156 --> 51:19.368
But I don't mind

51:21.371 --> 51:23.872
Just come home

51:26.709 --> 51:27.709
Come home

51:27.794 --> 51:29.544
Where you headin'?

51:29.629 --> 51:31.546
- Where you headin'?
- Las Vegas.

51:31.631 --> 51:34.466
Not from here you ain't. Not tonight.

51:34.550 --> 51:36.510
Let me see your ticket.

51:41.224 --> 51:44.059
- What time do you got?
- Five to 1 1 :00.

51:44.143 --> 51:48.271
The ticket office said that there was a bus
going to Las Vegas, Bay 3, at 1 1 :00.

51:48.356 --> 51:52.150
Well, now all we know for sure is that your watch
ain't being completely honest with you.

51:52.235 --> 51:54.778
There was a bus at 1 1 :00,
but now it's nearly 1 2:00.

51:54.862 --> 51:56.780
- 1 2:00?
- Where you just come from?

51:56.864 --> 51:59.741
New York through Chicago, Denver.

51:59.826 --> 52:02.744
Seems like you put your watch back
one too many times, my friend.

52:02.829 --> 52:07.040
There ain't no way you gonna catch a bus
that left here an hour ago.

52:07.125 --> 52:11.044
- There's no other bus.
- There's no other bus, not this time of night.

52:11.129 --> 52:14.381
There's a truck stop
a hundred yards up the road.

52:14.465 --> 52:18.427
Ifyou're lucky, you might pick up a lift
and catch the night train.

52:18.511 --> 52:20.429
Okay. Thank you.

52:26.060 --> 52:29.312
And all I'm wondering, why is this guy
trying to see his whole family...

52:29.397 --> 52:31.481
all over the country,
all in the same trip?

52:31.566 --> 52:36.111
- Well, I'm not dying, if that's what you're thinking.
- Hey, I'm not thinkin' anything.

52:36.195 --> 52:38.864
I'm just trying to visit the kids
and surprise them.

52:38.948 --> 52:42.159
Their mother's always kept
an eye on 'em, and...

52:42.243 --> 52:44.411
now it's up to me, so—

52:44.495 --> 52:47.664
- You lost your wife.
- About eight months ago.

52:47.749 --> 52:51.752
I lost my husband. J ust over a year now.

52:51.836 --> 52:54.504
I lost him to drink,
but it was my fault.

52:54.589 --> 52:56.506
I was stupid.

52:56.591 --> 52:58.925
Ignored all the signs,
you know how you do.

53:00.970 --> 53:03.597
I listen to that radio
all day in this cab.

53:03.681 --> 53:06.850
We got ourselves
an epidemic goin' on out there—

53:06.934 --> 53:11.271
you know, people eatin' too much,
drinkin' too much, killing themselves, basically...

53:11.355 --> 53:14.733
makin' up excuses all along the way.

53:14.817 --> 53:18.695
- I guess facing up to the truth ain't always easy.
- No.

53:18.780 --> 53:23.158
- Yeah, people like things easy. That's what they're used to.
- Yeah.

53:23.242 --> 53:24.993
No one likes to get hurt.

53:29.457 --> 53:30.457
No.

53:31.834 --> 53:33.752
Nobody likes to get hurt.

53:33.836 --> 53:38.256
I stop off in Reno. There's a night train from there,
gets you into Vegas in the morning.

53:38.341 --> 53:42.135
Otherwise, there's a cheap little motel
where I shut down ifyou don't wanna...

53:42.220 --> 53:44.930
travel through the night.

53:50.686 --> 53:53.271
Don't get all shy on me.
That wasn't a proposition.

53:53.356 --> 53:56.817
- No, I'm going to—
- Yeah. I sleep in the truck, all right?

54:03.032 --> 54:05.450
Take care, Frank.

54:05.535 --> 54:07.494
I appreciate it. Thank you.

54:36.149 --> 54:38.775
- Are you all right?
- Don't touch me.

54:38.860 --> 54:41.862
- I'm not touching anybody. I'm just—
- Don't touch me.

54:43.739 --> 54:44.865
You okay?

54:46.033 --> 54:48.618
Do your parents know where you are?

54:48.703 --> 54:53.165
- If I give you some money, will you eat something?
- Yeah, I'm clean, man.

54:53.249 --> 54:56.459
- Do you need some money?
- I could use some money.

54:56.544 --> 54:59.254
- I mean, everyone can use some money, right?
- Okay.

54:59.338 --> 55:01.631
Here—

55:01.716 --> 55:05.010
Here you go. Here.

55:07.805 --> 55:10.765
- You're okay?
- Yeah, what's with the questions?

55:10.850 --> 55:13.768
- You could say thank you.
- I could what?

55:13.853 --> 55:18.148
You could say thank you. I gave you some money.
You could say thank you.

55:18.232 --> 55:20.275
Hey, you're right.

55:20.359 --> 55:22.277
I'm sorry, man. You're right. Yeah, I—

55:22.361 --> 55:25.280
I forgot my manners. You got
a couple hundred dollars in there, and...

55:25.364 --> 55:27.073
this is my thanks.

55:42.173 --> 55:44.090
You need that?

55:46.219 --> 55:50.096
Please don't do anything.
I need— That's my medication.

55:51.098 --> 55:52.098
No—

56:05.196 --> 56:07.405
God, no.

56:46.487 --> 56:48.113
I'm not here at the moment...

56:48.197 --> 56:50.740
and Frank is probably in the garden.

56:50.825 --> 56:53.118
Leave a message, and I'll call you back.

57:44.253 --> 57:46.212
David.

57:48.549 --> 57:53.303
David? Of all my children, you're the one
that I worry about the most.

57:53.387 --> 57:54.596
I'm trying, Dad.

57:58.809 --> 58:00.518
- Dad!
- David!

58:01.645 --> 58:03.897
Tell me when I can see you.

58:09.862 --> 58:12.364
Dad!

58:21.248 --> 58:23.792
- Robert, Dad wasn't on the bus.
- What?

58:23.876 --> 58:27.003
I met the 1 0:00 bus like you said,
and everyone else got off...

58:27.088 --> 58:29.005
but he's not on it.

58:29.090 --> 58:32.008
Well—
Well, did you look in the station?

58:32.093 --> 58:34.260
- I mean, where have you looked?
- Yeah, of course. I looked everywhere.

58:34.970 --> 58:38.056
I don't know what to tell you.
He was due on the 1 0:00.

58:38.140 --> 58:40.100
So how can he not be on it?

58:41.769 --> 58:44.604
- Are you all right, Frank?
- Listen. The damnedest thing happened.

58:44.688 --> 58:46.856
I was brushing my teeth this morning...

58:46.941 --> 58:49.818
and I left my bottle of pills
right on the edge ofthe sink.

58:49.902 --> 58:53.530
Well, I knocked the whole thing right into the sink,
and it got all wet. There's nothing left.

58:53.614 --> 58:56.699
- The sink? Geez. Goddamn it. You're as bad as me.
- The sink. The damnedest thing.

58:56.784 --> 59:00.412
I'll write a new prescription, all right?
Just pop in. I'll leave it in the reception.

59:00.496 --> 59:05.708
Is that the only way to get them,
to go to reception? I have to come—

59:05.793 --> 59:08.962
I have to come in?
No, the garden is doing great. I'm—

59:09.046 --> 59:11.548
It's doing— I'm looking right at it.

59:11.632 --> 59:13.591
Looking really good. Really good.

59:17.471 --> 59:20.849
- Hello?
- Hey, it's me. You home?

59:20.933 --> 59:23.643
No. I'm waiting for you. Where are you?

59:23.727 --> 59:25.687
- He told you I was coming, didn't he?
- No.

59:25.771 --> 59:29.149
I told him not to tell you
I was coming, and he told you.

59:43.706 --> 59:46.291
- Hi, Dad.
- Yeah. Hi, glamour girl.

59:50.004 --> 59:51.963
- Welcome to Vegas, Dad.
- Yeah, thanks.

59:55.092 --> 59:57.260
Papa loves mambo

59:57.344 --> 59:59.304
I didn't order a stretch.

59:59.388 --> 1:00:01.389
I just wanted something comfortable.

1:00:01.474 --> 1:00:03.850
Good. No, it's got plenty
of leg room, that's for sure.

1:00:03.934 --> 1:00:06.311
That's why they call it a stretch?

1:00:06.395 --> 1:00:08.563
- I missed you.
- Oh, I miss you.

1:00:08.647 --> 1:00:12.192
- I've been worried about you.
- Don't. No. Tell me about your show.

1:00:12.276 --> 1:00:15.278
- Okay. We were at the Bellagio—
- Uh-huh.

1:00:15.362 --> 1:00:17.614
and it was a big production...

1:00:17.698 --> 1:00:20.617
- lots of underwater dance scenes.
- Uh-huh.

1:00:20.701 --> 1:00:23.328
And I was the mermaid, the lead.

1:00:23.412 --> 1:00:25.830
- Of course.
- And you would've loved it.

1:00:25.915 --> 1:00:29.667
- When could I go?
- It finished last week.

1:00:29.752 --> 1:00:31.252
- It finished?
- Yeah.

1:00:31.337 --> 1:00:34.672
Next time you have to fly out
and come see me. I just—

1:00:34.757 --> 1:00:38.468
I didn't want to bother you this time,
because I knew that you weren't feeling well.

1:00:38.552 --> 1:00:40.803
- But look at you.
- No, look at you.

1:00:40.888 --> 1:00:44.599
A dancer in a Las Vegas show on the big stage?
Just what you always wanted.

1:00:44.683 --> 1:00:46.643
Are you happy?

1:00:46.727 --> 1:00:48.645
- Very happy.
- Yeah?

1:00:48.729 --> 1:00:52.774
So, the only thing missing now
is— anything?

1:00:52.858 --> 1:00:55.026
- A man. I know.
- Well—

1:00:55.110 --> 1:00:58.112
- Papa loves mambo
- Papa loves mambo

1:00:58.197 --> 1:01:01.074
- Mama loves mambo
- Mama loves mambo

1:01:01.158 --> 1:01:03.952
Havin' their fling again
Younger than spring again

1:01:04.036 --> 1:01:06.496
Feelin' that zing again, wow

1:01:06.580 --> 1:01:08.581
This is where you live?

1:01:08.666 --> 1:01:12.418
- No, this is an elevator.
- Very good.

1:01:12.503 --> 1:01:16.005
I think you'll like the apartment.
It's very spacious.

1:01:16.090 --> 1:01:18.633
- Well, I'm happy sleeping on a couch.
- Really?

1:01:18.717 --> 1:01:20.760
- Really.
- Okay.

1:01:24.807 --> 1:01:26.766
- Wow.
- You like it?

1:01:26.850 --> 1:01:28.810
- It's—
- Very me?

1:01:28.894 --> 1:01:31.271
Very you. Very impressive.

1:01:35.651 --> 1:01:38.486
- Well, do you want to see your room?
- Sure.

1:01:38.571 --> 1:01:40.989
Okay. Come on.

1:01:41.073 --> 1:01:46.202
So, bed or sofa? Sofa or bed?

1:01:46.287 --> 1:01:48.079
This is my room.

1:01:48.581 --> 1:01:50.456
It's huge.

1:01:50.541 --> 1:01:53.543
- Look at that television.
- I know.

1:01:53.627 --> 1:01:56.462
I booked us dinner at a place
called the Stratosphere.

1:01:56.547 --> 1:01:58.464
- Do you know what that is?
- No.

1:01:58.549 --> 1:02:03.219
- It's a revolving restaurant 800 feet above the ground.
- No, stay just like that.

1:02:03.304 --> 1:02:04.804
Okay.

1:02:04.888 --> 1:02:06.764
Okay. One more time.

1:02:06.849 --> 1:02:09.017
I'll just get that.
Stay there. I'll be right back.

1:02:09.101 --> 1:02:11.019
Okay. Just gonna take another picture.

1:02:13.022 --> 1:02:15.690
- Jilly, hi.
- H i. How are you?

1:02:15.774 --> 1:02:17.734
- Good. Come on in. I want—
- I need a favor.

1:02:17.818 --> 1:02:20.653
I have to go pick up Paul from the airport,
and I haven't got the car seat.

1:02:20.738 --> 1:02:22.697
- I want you to meet my dad.
- Oh, great. Hi.

1:02:22.781 --> 1:02:24.907
- H i.
- Dad...

1:02:24.992 --> 1:02:26.951
this is my friend J illy.

1:02:27.036 --> 1:02:28.536
- Hi.
- What?

1:02:28.621 --> 1:02:30.830
- J illy. It's a pleasure to meet you.
- Hi, J illy.

1:02:30.914 --> 1:02:33.958
- How you doin'?
- How are you doing? Who's this guy?

1:02:34.043 --> 1:02:36.794
This is Max,
and we could really use a favor.

1:02:36.879 --> 1:02:39.422
Could you watch him for a few hours?

1:02:39.506 --> 1:02:42.967
Yeah, well, the only thing is that we
were gonna head out later for dinner.

1:02:43.052 --> 1:02:45.970
You know? It's fine. I'm gonna pop downstairs.
I can see if Helen's around.

1:02:46.055 --> 1:02:49.265
- We could stay in, ifyou want.
- I think you guys should go out. It's your-

1:02:49.350 --> 1:02:52.769
- No, you're tired. It's fine.
- I'm easy. I'm easy. Whatever. Whatever it is.

1:02:52.853 --> 1:02:56.022
- We'll take him. Here. Give him to me.
- You sure? Oh, thank you so much.

1:02:56.106 --> 1:02:58.691
I should be back in time
for you guys to go out anyway.

1:02:58.776 --> 1:03:00.985
It'll just be a couple of hours.
But thank you again.

1:03:03.405 --> 1:03:05.948
Okay— Yeah, it's fine.

1:03:06.033 --> 1:03:08.117
Well, I can bathe him.

1:03:08.702 --> 1:03:11.621
Okay. I'll call
if I need anything, honestly.

1:03:11.705 --> 1:03:15.041
I'll be all right. Okay.

1:03:15.125 --> 1:03:16.709
Bye.

1:03:17.795 --> 1:03:20.296
Slight problem.

1:03:20.381 --> 1:03:22.298
- Jilly?
- Yeah.

1:03:22.383 --> 1:03:24.967
Paul's flight was canceled—

1:03:25.052 --> 1:03:27.679
so he's stuck in LA,
and she's going to pick him up.

1:03:27.763 --> 1:03:30.973
So that means we have Max for the night.

1:03:31.058 --> 1:03:32.975
Okay.

1:03:33.060 --> 1:03:36.354
- Is that okay?
- It's okay.

1:03:36.438 --> 1:03:39.482
What's the matter? What's the matter?

1:04:15.310 --> 1:04:19.063
Okay, just stay up.
Give me your arm.

1:04:19.148 --> 1:04:22.525
- Do you want me to get that?
- No, Dad, just leave it. It's fine.

1:04:22.609 --> 1:04:25.945
- Okay.
- Thanks.

1:04:27.406 --> 1:04:31.951
Hi. I'm not here right now,
so please leave me a message.

1:04:33.704 --> 1:04:37.540
It's me. Look, I need the apartment back
sooner than I thought...

1:04:37.624 --> 1:04:40.793
so call me.

1:04:41.879 --> 1:04:44.338
Stop splashing.

1:05:01.815 --> 1:05:03.941
A nice apartment.

1:05:04.026 --> 1:05:07.487
Yeah, it's a little big though.

1:05:07.571 --> 1:05:11.324
- You bought it?
- No, I'm renting it, but I got a good deal.

1:05:18.207 --> 1:05:21.459
Listen. I'm gonna leave tomorrow.
I'm gonna go back home.

1:05:21.543 --> 1:05:25.213
- But you just got here.
- I know, but it's been a long trip.

1:05:25.297 --> 1:05:28.758
I'm running low on my medication.
I just thought I would—

1:05:28.842 --> 1:05:31.427
Well, can't we get you a refill?

1:05:33.013 --> 1:05:35.640
It's been a long trip, honey.

1:05:39.353 --> 1:05:42.146
Yeah. You look tired.

1:05:42.231 --> 1:05:44.982
I'm okay. I should get home.

1:05:45.067 --> 1:05:46.859
Would you be okay with that?

1:05:48.362 --> 1:05:50.738
Yeah— Of course.

1:05:50.823 --> 1:05:53.825
You should do what you want.

1:05:53.909 --> 1:05:55.910
Here, take that.

1:05:59.498 --> 1:06:01.541
I was thinking of flying.

1:06:01.625 --> 1:06:03.876
- You never fly.
- I know.

1:06:11.009 --> 1:06:13.010
Thank you.

1:06:14.805 --> 1:06:16.806
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

1:06:20.978 --> 1:06:23.396
You didn't really want
to eat out, did you?

1:06:24.898 --> 1:06:29.569
No, I didn't, not 800 feet above the ground
in a revolving restaurant.

1:06:38.120 --> 1:06:40.746
Remember when your mother
taught you how to eat spaghetti?

1:06:42.541 --> 1:06:44.000
Yep.

1:06:49.006 --> 1:06:52.675
Sometimes I pick up the phone
to dial her number...

1:06:52.759 --> 1:06:54.635
and then I remember.

1:06:57.264 --> 1:06:59.223
Keep calling next time.

1:06:59.308 --> 1:07:02.184
The number's still the same,
and I'm still on the other end.

1:07:03.186 --> 1:07:05.062
- Okay.
- Yeah?

1:07:05.147 --> 1:07:07.148
- Yes.
- I don't know what it is with you kids.

1:07:07.232 --> 1:07:09.692
You always told your mother everything.
You never told me anything.

1:07:09.776 --> 1:07:11.694
You were always on the phone with her.

1:07:12.946 --> 1:07:16.324
I'd pick up the phone. I'd say hello,
you'd say, "H i, Dad. Mom there?"

1:07:16.408 --> 1:07:19.952
It wasn't that bad. It was just that...

1:07:20.037 --> 1:07:23.873
Mom was easier to talk to, and you always worried
so much if everything wasn't perfect.

1:07:23.957 --> 1:07:25.833
No. That's not true.

1:07:27.878 --> 1:07:29.795
We could just talk to Mom.

1:07:29.880 --> 1:07:33.382
- Oh, but you couldn't talk to me?
- Well, she was a good listener.

1:07:33.467 --> 1:07:35.509
You were a good talker.

1:07:35.594 --> 1:07:37.678
Well, so that's good. We made a good team.

1:07:38.972 --> 1:07:40.640
Yeah.

1:07:42.059 --> 1:07:45.144
You wouldn't change anything, would you?

1:07:46.688 --> 1:07:48.773
You pushed us pretty hard.

1:07:48.857 --> 1:07:52.985
No. That's not true.

1:07:54.321 --> 1:07:56.948
You didn't all
feel that way, did you?

1:07:57.032 --> 1:08:00.326
I think David felt it the most.

1:08:01.328 --> 1:08:03.329
Yeah.

1:08:07.459 --> 1:08:08.960
I can see that.

1:08:09.836 --> 1:08:12.922
He so never wanted to let you down.

1:08:14.007 --> 1:08:18.135
I know. I was never any harder
on him as far as I could see.

1:08:18.220 --> 1:08:20.763
You were all different,
and look at him today.

1:08:22.641 --> 1:08:25.851
- Did I tell you I went to see him in New York?
- No.

1:08:25.936 --> 1:08:28.145
Yeah. He wasn't there,
but I saw some of his artwork...

1:08:28.230 --> 1:08:30.147
downstairs in the gallery
below his apartment.

1:08:30.232 --> 1:08:32.692
It was right there on display.
It was just... beautiful.

1:08:34.361 --> 1:08:37.405
So look what happened to him.
He turned out okay.

1:08:37.489 --> 1:08:39.448
You turned out okay.

1:08:39.533 --> 1:08:42.660
I don't know, Dad.

1:08:42.744 --> 1:08:45.371
How can you say that? Look at you.

1:08:45.455 --> 1:08:48.958
You've wanted to be a dancer
ever since you were a little girl.

1:08:49.042 --> 1:08:51.752
You were gifted, and nobody pushed you.

1:08:51.837 --> 1:08:53.879
- What about your plans?
- It all worked out.

1:08:53.964 --> 1:08:56.424
What did you want to be
when you were my age?

1:08:57.509 --> 1:08:59.635
I didn't have any plans.

1:08:59.720 --> 1:09:04.223
I just wanted to hold down a job and find somebody
crazy enough to marry me— your mother.

1:09:04.975 --> 1:09:09.020
I don't know. But when you guys came along,
things were different.

1:09:09.104 --> 1:09:12.314
There were opportunities. What kind of father
would I have been if I hadn't pushed you?

1:09:12.399 --> 1:09:15.401
So there wasn't anything
you wanted to achieve?

1:09:15.485 --> 1:09:20.614
No, I didn't really think much about it.
I never really gave it much thought.

1:09:20.699 --> 1:09:24.160
All I wanted to do was just be
a good father, that's all.

1:09:36.006 --> 1:09:38.049
- You've got your boarding pass.
- All right.

1:09:38.133 --> 1:09:42.845
And you're all checked in,
and we know your gate.

1:09:42.929 --> 1:09:44.847
So?

1:09:44.931 --> 1:09:48.142
- I'll come visit you as soon as I can. I promise.
- Oh, I'd like that.

1:09:48.226 --> 1:09:51.520
I wanna get us all around
the same table together.

1:09:51.605 --> 1:09:54.398
- At Christmas.
- Or before. It's up to you.

1:09:54.483 --> 1:09:57.359
Great. Count me in.

1:09:57.444 --> 1:10:01.197
Here.

1:10:01.281 --> 1:10:05.367
- What's this?
- I had to give it to each ofyou.

1:10:05.452 --> 1:10:07.995
- Well, shall I open it?
- No, open it later.

1:10:08.080 --> 1:10:11.207
- Are you sure?
- Sure I'm sure.

1:10:11.291 --> 1:10:16.295
Okay.

1:10:19.800 --> 1:10:22.968
- Be good.
- J ust for you.

1:10:26.556 --> 1:10:29.058
- Be good.
- I will.

1:10:42.322 --> 1:10:43.823
Bye, Dad.

1:10:54.042 --> 1:10:56.043
Have a good flight.

1:11:21.153 --> 1:11:22.778
Rosie, where's Dad?

1:11:22.863 --> 1:11:25.614
He's on his way home. I just left him.

1:11:25.699 --> 1:11:27.950
What did you find out?

1:11:28.034 --> 1:11:30.870
David was caught
buying some drugs in a bar.

1:11:30.954 --> 1:11:33.622
- No!
- And he got sick so quickly that they now think...

1:11:33.707 --> 1:11:36.625
he may have panicked and swallowed some of
the drugs when he was arrested.

1:11:36.710 --> 1:11:40.921
- Is he okay? Have you seen him?
- Not yet. He was taken to a hospital.

1:11:41.006 --> 1:11:44.675
- I'm there now, but they're not being very helpful.
- What do you mean?

1:11:44.759 --> 1:11:47.636
I keep asking if he's here,
but I can't get a straight answer.

1:11:47.721 --> 1:11:50.639
Listen. The lawyer's with me, and the guy
from the embassy's here.

1:11:50.724 --> 1:11:55.227
Call Robert. I promised I'd call him
before his concert, tell him what's going on.

1:11:55.312 --> 1:11:57.521
Can you do that for me?

1:11:57.606 --> 1:11:59.607
Yeah.

1:12:12.871 --> 1:12:16.790
Excuse me.
How much longer before we land?

1:12:16.875 --> 1:12:20.252
Forty minutes. But there's a storm,
so it might take a little longer.

1:12:20.337 --> 1:12:24.340
- A storm?
- It's okay. We go around it, not through it.

1:12:24.424 --> 1:12:27.301
- Can I have some more water please?
- Sure.

1:12:33.266 --> 1:12:34.808
Excuse me.

1:12:46.279 --> 1:12:49.531
Ladies and gentlemen, the captain
has turned on the seat belt sign...

1:12:49.616 --> 1:12:52.952
so we ask that you please
return to your seats as soon as possible.

1:12:57.499 --> 1:13:00.793
Sir, you need to push
your table up. Thank you.

1:13:08.802 --> 1:13:10.552
Sir, is everything all right?

1:13:20.355 --> 1:13:23.649
Sir, okay. Sir? Sir, you're gonna be fine.

1:13:23.733 --> 1:13:25.651
You're gonna be fine. J ust breathe for me.

1:13:25.735 --> 1:13:27.444
You're gonna be fine.

1:13:29.656 --> 1:13:32.866
Come on. It's ready. Everybody sit down.

1:13:32.951 --> 1:13:34.868
Hey, David? Come on.

1:13:35.912 --> 1:13:37.788
Thank you.

1:13:38.999 --> 1:13:40.916
How come you're home, Dad?

1:13:41.001 --> 1:13:43.836
- I took the day offwork.
- But you'd never do that.

1:13:43.920 --> 1:13:46.672
I know, but I wanted to spend
some time with you guys.

1:13:46.756 --> 1:13:49.883
- Is anything wrong?
- No, nothing is wrong.

1:13:49.968 --> 1:13:53.679
Well, you know, actually,
there is something.

1:13:55.181 --> 1:13:57.349
You know, I've been
asking myself a question.

1:13:57.434 --> 1:14:00.477
It's been like a puzzle,
and I can't figure it out.

1:14:00.562 --> 1:14:02.855
Let's stop eating for a minute.

1:14:06.443 --> 1:14:11.989
I keep asking myself why you all lied to me.
All ofyou.

1:14:12.073 --> 1:14:16.452
Amy, Jeffwore the same shirt to work
the morning after I stayed.

1:14:16.536 --> 1:14:18.203
He doesn't live with you anymore, does he?

1:14:19.873 --> 1:14:22.124
He left home about three months ago.

1:14:22.208 --> 1:14:24.877
There's another woman.
That's whyJack hates him.

1:14:24.961 --> 1:14:28.005
When that man Tom came over to me
at the station and shook my hand...

1:14:28.089 --> 1:14:30.424
he wanted to make
an impression, didn't he?

1:14:30.508 --> 1:14:33.385
You pulled that chair out before he came over
'cause you were expecting him.

1:14:33.470 --> 1:14:35.387
Tom was waiting at the station.

1:14:35.472 --> 1:14:39.391
I wanted to know that you'd met him.
I didn't want to miss the opportunity.

1:14:39.476 --> 1:14:43.520
In case I get sick
and we never get the chance to meet?

1:14:53.281 --> 1:14:56.700
- Robert—
- I think we should go in. I think I felt some rain.

1:14:56.785 --> 1:14:59.161
There were posters all over the city.
You weren't going to Europe.

1:14:59.245 --> 1:15:02.039
You weren't even performing that night.
We could have spent time together.

1:15:02.123 --> 1:15:05.292
- But you lied to me. You didn't wanna be with me.
- The truth is, Dad...

1:15:05.377 --> 1:15:07.920
there are lots of things
that we don't tell you.

1:15:08.505 --> 1:15:10.881
But that doesn't mean
that we want to hurt you.

1:15:10.965 --> 1:15:12.674
Mom didn't always tell you everything,
and you know that.

1:15:12.759 --> 1:15:16.220
Don't blame your mother for this.
And wipe your mouth.

1:15:17.764 --> 1:15:20.557
Rosie, the baby is yours, isn't it?

1:15:23.436 --> 1:15:25.396
I was goin' to tell you.

1:15:25.480 --> 1:15:27.564
Go on.

1:15:27.649 --> 1:15:30.109
- Tell him the rest.
- Robert, shut up.

1:15:30.193 --> 1:15:32.861
- Go on. I'll tell him.
- Shut up.

1:15:32.946 --> 1:15:37.449
- She doesn't know if she likes boys or girls.
- Robert, stop it.

1:15:37.534 --> 1:15:39.451
Did your mother know you were pregnant?

1:15:41.913 --> 1:15:44.915
And she kept it from me.
Why would she do that?

1:15:44.999 --> 1:15:46.500
We were goin' to tell you...

1:15:46.584 --> 1:15:49.962
but then Mom got sick...

1:15:50.046 --> 1:15:52.297
and I didn't want to disappoint you.

1:15:55.927 --> 1:16:01.265
David, do you still live in New York
at that apartment?

1:16:01.349 --> 1:16:03.475
- No.
- Then where can I find you?

1:16:03.560 --> 1:16:04.560
I can't tell you.

1:16:04.644 --> 1:16:07.229
Tell me where I can find you
and when I can see you.

1:16:07.313 --> 1:16:10.774
- I don't want to see you, Dad.
- Then stop— Do not laugh at me.

1:16:12.068 --> 1:16:13.193
Tell me the truth.

1:16:14.821 --> 1:16:18.323
And wipe that smirk offyour face.
Wipe the smirk offyour face.

1:16:18.408 --> 1:16:21.577
I have your skateboard in the shed there.
I know exactly where it is.

1:16:21.661 --> 1:16:23.787
I'll burn the damn thing, you hear me?

1:16:23.872 --> 1:16:26.874
- You took my forward wheels.
- Don't laugh. Don't laugh! Quiet!

1:16:26.958 --> 1:16:30.377
After everything I've done for you,
this is all you can do— is laugh?

1:16:30.462 --> 1:16:33.922
When I'm asking you about
something that's worrying me?

1:16:34.007 --> 1:16:36.425
Jesus! David.

1:16:36.509 --> 1:16:40.721
Your mother always asked me why I was
so hard on you. This is why. This is exactly why!

1:16:40.805 --> 1:16:43.307
Have some respect!

1:16:55.361 --> 1:16:57.654
So what am I supposed to do?

1:16:57.739 --> 1:17:01.658
Act as though nothing's wrong.
That's what Mom did. It's best for all of us.

1:17:01.743 --> 1:17:05.037
I can't do that. I can't act as if nothing happened.
What do I tell your mother?

1:17:05.163 --> 1:17:08.916
- What do I say?
- Anyway, she won't ask you anything, 'cause she's dead.

1:17:09.000 --> 1:17:10.417
David!

1:17:19.344 --> 1:17:23.222
- That's it. I've had enough. I'm outta here.
- Me too. I'm outta here.

1:17:23.306 --> 1:17:24.806
Come on!

1:17:26.643 --> 1:17:29.478
- Tell her nothing.
- How can I do that?

1:17:29.562 --> 1:17:32.523
Ifyou love her as she loves you...

1:17:32.607 --> 1:17:35.442
then you'll tell her
what she wants to hear.

1:17:35.527 --> 1:17:38.195
Tell her that we're all fine.

1:18:41.175 --> 1:18:43.176
Dad.

1:19:05.617 --> 1:19:09.828
At last.
Finally have my family in the same room.

1:19:12.665 --> 1:19:16.418
- Is David here?
- Rosie's here, and Robert.

1:19:16.502 --> 1:19:19.713
- How are you feeling?
- Was it a heart attack?

1:19:19.797 --> 1:19:22.341
They're not sure.

1:19:23.426 --> 1:19:25.344
Amy, is he telling the truth?

1:19:25.428 --> 1:19:27.763
The doctors are waiting
for some test results.

1:19:27.847 --> 1:19:32.017
Oh, come on. Don't lie to me.

1:19:32.101 --> 1:19:37.689
Why do I always find it so hard
to believe all ofyou now? Come on.

1:19:39.442 --> 1:19:41.693
They suspected a heart attack.

1:19:41.778 --> 1:19:44.988
They ran some tests...

1:19:45.073 --> 1:19:48.659
and they got the results.

1:19:48.743 --> 1:19:51.078
And it was a heart attack.

1:19:51.162 --> 1:19:55.666
- A mild one.
- Good. A start, at least.

1:19:55.750 --> 1:19:59.127
I didn't want to worry you
until you had a chance to...

1:19:59.212 --> 1:20:01.171
come to terms with what happened.

1:20:02.507 --> 1:20:05.467
You can worry me, all ofyou.

1:20:05.551 --> 1:20:08.720
I'm a father of four. I expect that.

1:20:08.805 --> 1:20:13.350
I know you all had problems.

1:20:14.811 --> 1:20:18.855
I know that, and I can see you've been
keeping things from me.

1:20:18.940 --> 1:20:23.110
- But right now there's something that I need—
- Dad, maybe you should rest.

1:20:23.194 --> 1:20:27.322
No, I will rest,
but I need an answer to a question.

1:20:27.407 --> 1:20:31.243
You were honest with your mother,
and I want you to be honest with me.

1:20:32.286 --> 1:20:35.747
It's all right, you know. I'm okay.

1:20:36.791 --> 1:20:38.792
I can handle it.

1:20:38.876 --> 1:20:42.629
I know David is in trouble...

1:20:42.714 --> 1:20:45.924
and I just want to know where he is...

1:20:47.301 --> 1:20:50.721
and how soon I can see him.

1:20:52.473 --> 1:20:55.350
So, who's gonna tell me?

1:20:55.435 --> 1:20:58.729
Why don't you take it—
Why don't you rest for a while?

1:20:59.731 --> 1:21:02.232
What is it?

1:21:05.737 --> 1:21:07.738
J ust tell me the truth.

1:21:09.115 --> 1:21:10.949
Dad, I'm sorry.

1:21:14.787 --> 1:21:16.955
David died, Dad.

1:21:17.749 --> 1:21:19.750
I'm sorry.

1:21:21.961 --> 1:21:25.797
No. That's not true.
Tell me that's not true.

1:21:25.882 --> 1:21:29.551
- I'm sorry, Dad.
- No.

1:21:29.635 --> 1:21:33.472
- He moved out of his apartment, and—
- No.

1:21:33.556 --> 1:21:35.849
we knew that he was traveling.

1:21:35.933 --> 1:21:39.811
And then we started
getting calls from Mexico.

1:21:39.896 --> 1:21:44.566
There was a lot of confusion.
We didn't want to tell you until we were sure.

1:21:45.568 --> 1:21:48.111
No. No. I—

1:21:48.196 --> 1:21:50.363
- He had a lot of problems.
- No. No.

1:21:50.448 --> 1:21:55.202
He wasn't happy, Dad.
He's been havin' a tough time since Mom died.

1:21:55.286 --> 1:21:57.954
We've all been worried about him.

1:21:58.039 --> 1:22:00.916
Yeah, but, you—

1:22:01.000 --> 1:22:03.126
Not for sure, I mean—

1:22:03.211 --> 1:22:06.505
It was Mexico. It could be anyone.
It could be a mistake.

1:22:06.589 --> 1:22:08.507
- They-
- It could be.

1:22:08.591 --> 1:22:14.221
I flew out there after you visited.

1:22:14.305 --> 1:22:18.183
That's why you couldn't stay.
That's why we all made excuses.

1:22:18.267 --> 1:22:21.269
No. No. Wrong—

1:22:21.354 --> 1:22:24.981
Not my son. That's not my son.

1:22:27.527 --> 1:22:28.860
No.

1:22:31.572 --> 1:22:34.199
They said it was an overdose.

1:22:41.958 --> 1:22:46.837
No. Not my son.
That's not my son.

1:22:46.921 --> 1:22:47.921
No.

1:23:17.243 --> 1:23:20.370
- What are you gonna do when you grow up?
- I want to be a painter and do my pictures.

1:23:20.454 --> 1:23:23.498
No, not a painter. Painters paint walls,
and dogs pee on walls.

1:23:23.583 --> 1:23:25.542
You're gonna be an artist.

1:23:25.626 --> 1:23:27.586
- You're gonna work hard?
- Yes, Dad.

1:23:27.670 --> 1:23:29.921
You gonna make me proud?

1:23:36.804 --> 1:23:39.931
I'm sorry about how
everything's worked out, Dad.

1:23:45.438 --> 1:23:48.273
It's not your fault.

1:23:53.237 --> 1:23:56.573
I've been thinkin'
about what I wanna do when I grow up.

1:23:56.657 --> 1:24:01.745
- Yeah? But what did you decide?
- I might still be an artist...

1:24:01.829 --> 1:24:04.998
or I might just do a normal job,
like a painter.

1:24:06.459 --> 1:24:10.211
- I'd be proud ofyou no matter what you did.
- Really?

1:24:10.296 --> 1:24:12.297
Really.

1:24:13.966 --> 1:24:15.967
Good.

1:24:18.804 --> 1:24:21.139
I told Mom I wouldn't be long.

1:24:23.559 --> 1:24:27.604
- Give her my love.
- I will.

1:24:29.857 --> 1:24:31.858
Well, I'll see you, Dad.

1:24:34.070 --> 1:24:35.445
David.

1:24:37.949 --> 1:24:39.574
I'm sorry.

1:24:43.955 --> 1:24:46.081
It's not your fault, Dad.

1:24:52.213 --> 1:24:58.843
David?

1:27:31.664 --> 1:27:34.624
Well, it was a big trip...

1:27:34.708 --> 1:27:38.878
and ifyou asked me what I've learned,
I'd have to tell you I'm not sure.

1:27:38.963 --> 1:27:45.176
I know if I could do it all over again,
I would ask less of the kids.

1:27:45.261 --> 1:27:48.138
As long as they were happy,
that would be fine with me.

1:27:50.266 --> 1:27:53.059
I know I have to stop thinking of them as
if they're still children.

1:27:53.144 --> 1:27:55.061
I can't tell them what to do anymore.

1:27:55.146 --> 1:27:57.772
They have to find their own way.

1:27:57.857 --> 1:27:59.440
And...

1:28:00.192 --> 1:28:01.818
sometimes...

1:28:03.112 --> 1:28:06.322
you talked to me about things
that I should have listened to you more carefully.

1:28:07.867 --> 1:28:11.661
You presented me with the details
of our children's lives...

1:28:14.373 --> 1:28:17.333
and I ignored them.

1:28:18.878 --> 1:28:20.879
And for that—

1:28:27.678 --> 1:28:30.972
But that isn't what you want to hear.
I know. What you want is the news.

1:28:31.056 --> 1:28:34.434
Well, the news is this:

1:28:34.518 --> 1:28:38.479
Robert, Amy and Rosie promised
to visit me for the holidays.

1:28:38.564 --> 1:28:41.566
And you know what?
This time I believe them.

1:28:42.735 --> 1:28:44.235
And David—

1:28:44.904 --> 1:28:45.904
David—

1:28:48.199 --> 1:28:50.283
I hope will spend Christmas with you.

1:28:57.708 --> 1:29:01.252
I went back to New York
to buy David's painting.

1:29:02.796 --> 1:29:05.924
The portrait— I know which one you mean,
but I'm afraid it's sold.

1:29:06.008 --> 1:29:08.009
It is sold?

1:29:12.264 --> 1:29:14.015
Were you familiar with the artist?

1:29:14.099 --> 1:29:18.770
Yeah, not as much as I would like
to have been, but yes.

1:29:18.854 --> 1:29:21.564
- Thank you.
- Why don't you give me your details?

1:29:21.649 --> 1:29:24.609
If anything of David's comes in,
I'll let you know.

1:29:26.528 --> 1:29:28.446
Excuse me. Excuse me.

1:29:29.949 --> 1:29:32.617
I just saw your name.
I'm stupid. I should have realized.

1:29:32.701 --> 1:29:34.577
That's okay.

1:29:35.829 --> 1:29:37.330
I'm sorry.

1:29:38.874 --> 1:29:42.210
You know, I knew David. He used to hang out
at the gallery all the time...

1:29:42.294 --> 1:29:46.965
and he used to say that if it wasn't for his dad,
that he never would've become an artist.

1:29:47.841 --> 1:29:51.177
He said he would've ended up painting
walls and that dogs pee on walls.

1:29:53.305 --> 1:29:56.975
Look, we might have something of his
in storage. I can check ifyou'd like.

1:29:57.685 --> 1:30:00.144
- Okay. Sure.
- Okay.

1:30:00.229 --> 1:30:03.439
And I won't pretend David's work
was very commercial—

1:30:04.316 --> 1:30:05.817
Oh, here it is.

1:30:07.278 --> 1:30:08.820
He had his own style...

1:30:09.571 --> 1:30:11.489
and he wasn't concerned with fashion...

1:30:18.872 --> 1:30:20.623
but for what it's worth...

1:30:21.834 --> 1:30:23.626
I thought he was really special.

1:30:41.312 --> 1:30:42.812
Thank you.

1:30:51.530 --> 1:30:54.615
Hello, this is Frank.
I'm not out—

1:30:54.700 --> 1:30:58.286
I mean—
I'm not here at the moment.

1:30:58.370 --> 1:31:02.040
I'm probably out shopping
for the holidays...

1:31:02.124 --> 1:31:04.292
but ifyou leave a message,
I will call you back.

1:31:04.376 --> 1:31:05.543
Thank you.

1:31:07.087 --> 1:31:10.131
Don't laugh, but I promised to cook
the turkey for the first time this year-

1:31:10.215 --> 1:31:12.759
Got the whole family coming.
What's the biggest bird you got?

1:31:12.843 --> 1:31:16.763
- Half a dozen of-
